---

Learning to type was perhaps the smartest thing I did when starting our learning to code in earnest.

It had a few profound effects.

It made me humble.

It made me slow down and accept that I was beginning at the very beginning.

It gave me something simple I could always practise and know that I was getting a bit closer to my goal, even if I didn't have any mental energy. I would sit and type along to the lyrics of music I was listening to.

This is powerful - it is powerful to tell yourself that you're not going to stop.

It's powerful meta-programming to send into your unconscious.

If you can convince your unconscious mind that you are not going to stop wanting something, that you're not going to stop pursuing it - then eventually your unconscious mind will start to help you out.

Because it's smart. It knows when it's beaten. Nothing in the world can defeat you once you've made up your mind not to quit.

There are only certain outcomes available still once the decision has been made.

